#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
carla_capture.py  –  Merged SUMO + CARLA AID Dataset Generator
================================================================
Single script that runs SUMO traffic simulation AND captures CARLA
camera images around incident events.

How it relates to simulation.py
---------------------------------
This script IMPORTS SUMOSimulator from simulation.py so all SUMO logic
(route generation, incident injection, detector logging, recovery detection)
is identical to the standalone SUMO pipeline.  Nothing is reimplemented.

What this script adds
----------------------
• CarlaManager  – headless CARLA process, camera, vehicle actor pool
• AIDScenarioRunner – wraps SUMOSimulator and hooks CARLA capture into
  the simulation loop at the right moments
• CSV output with per-frame metadata (scenario_id, sim_time, label, ...)
  ready to join against the SUMO macro data in train/val/test HDF5 files

Label design (no post-recovery ambiguity)
------------------------------------------
  label = 0  →  PRE-incident frames (PRE_INCIDENT_WINDOW seconds before injection)
  label = 1  →  incident ACTIVE (vehicle stopped)
  Scenario camera capture STOPS at incident_clear_time.

  Residual traffic jam frames (vehicle recovered but queue still present)
  are intentionally excluded.  Including them with label=0 would teach the
  CNN that "queue = normal", which harms precision.

Merging with SUMO macro data
------------------------------
  Join key:  scenario_id  +  sim_time
  For the 30-second history window, select SUMO detector rows where:
      scenario_id == frame.scenario_id  AND
      sim_time    IN [frame.sim_time - 30, frame.sim_time]

CNN recommendation
------------------
  EfficientNet-B0  (best accuracy/FLOPs ratio for 384x640, ImageNet pretrain)
  ResNet-18        (simpler, easier Grad-CAM, slightly lower accuracy)
  Avoid MobileNetV3 unless deploying on embedded hardware.

Usage
-----
  python carla_capture.py                # run all incident scenarios
  python carla_capture.py --dry-run      # SUMO only, no CARLA (fast validation)
  python carla_capture.py --limit 1      # run first scenario only
  python carla_capture.py --split-only   # rebuild train/val/test CSVs only
"""

